==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embrocation
<hw>Em`bro*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>embrocatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>embrocation</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The act of moistening and rubbing a
diseased part with spirit, oil, etc.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The liquid
or lotion with which an affected part is rubbed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embroglio</ent>⟦br⟧
